<p>I wind the car windows down, always. It is a small act, insignificant, though it feels like an act of defiance. The wind tangles my hair. I don't care. Ah, sweet, sweet Summer! May this euphoria never wear off, the newfound ability to drive.</p>

<p>Today, strawberries: $3 for two. A steal. The run, a return to my body. The library, long-overdue fashion magazines I read a few pages of. All the little tasks that, together, make a life. In the car, <a href="https://open.spotify.com/track/7nvD9cQj5wYGY44Mhh3My3" target="_blank"><i>Magnetising</i></a> plays: a song like velvet stretched thin over wire. I am someone else now: a French spy with a cigarette in her mouth, driving a stolen car. I am invincible.</p>



